  "conditionals": 37,
  "created": "2025-10-08",
  "description": "The nitrogen regulation (Ntr) system controls assimilation of nitrogen from poor sources (glutamine, arginine, etc.) when ammonia is limiting. This sophisticated regulatory cascade involves the two-component system NtrB-NtrC, the alternative sigma factor \u03c354 (RpoN), and the PII signal transduction protein GlnB. The system demonstrates phosphorelay signaling, \u03c354-dependent transcription activation, and integration of nitrogen status with global metabolism.",
  "id": "ecoli_nitrogen_assimilation",
  "keywords": [
    "nitrogen regulation",
    "Ntr system",
    "NtrB",
    "NtrC",
    "sigma-54",
    "PII protein",
    "glutamine synthetase",
    "two-component system",
    "nitrogen assimilation",
    "enhancer-binding protein"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-08",
  "logicGates": {
    "and": 3,
    "not": 0,
    "or": 1
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Nitrogen Status Input\n    A[Ammonia Limitation] --> B[Low Nitrogen Signal]\n    C[Glutamine Depletion] --> D[Nitrogen Starvation]\n    B --> E[Reduced NH4+ Availability]\n    D --> E\n    \n    %% PII Protein Modification\n    E --> F[PII Protein GlnB]\n    F --> G[Low Glutamine]\n    G --> H[2-Ketoglutarate Accumulation]\n    H --> I[2-KG Binds PII]\n    I --> J[PII Conformational Change]\n    J --> K[PII-T Active Form]\n    \n    %% Decision: Nitrogen Status\n    K --> L{Nitrogen<br/>Limitation?}\n    \n    %% NtrB Kinase Activation\n    L -->|Yes| M[PII-T Releases NtrB]\n    M --> N[NtrB Kinase Activity]\n    N --> O[ATP Binding]\n    O --> P[NtrB Autophosphorylation]\n    P --> Q[NtrB-P Formation]\n    \n    %% Phosphotransfer to NtrC\n    Q --> R[Phosphotransfer to NtrC]\n    R --> S[NtrC-P Active Form]\n    S --> T[NtrC-P Oligomerization]\n    T --> U[NtrC-P Enhancer Binding]\n    \n    %% \u03c354 Recruitment\n    V[\u03c354 RpoN] --> W[\u03c354 Binds glnA Promoter]\n    W --> X[RNAP-\u03c354 Complex]\n    X --> Y[Closed Complex]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 1: \u03c354 Activation\n    U --> ANDGATE1{NtrC-P Enhancer AND<br/>RNAP-\u03c354 Complex?}\n    Y --> ANDGATE1\n    \n    %% ATP-Dependent Activation\n    ANDGATE1 -->|Yes| Z[NtrC-P Contacts \u03c354]\n    Z --> AA[ATP Hydrolysis]\n    AA --> AB[DNA Melting]\n    AB --> AC[Open Complex Formation]\n    AC --> AD[Transcription Initiation]\n    \n    %% glnA Expression\n    AD --> AE[glnA mRNA Synthesis]\n    AE --> AF[glnA Translation]\n    AF --> AG[Glutamine Synthetase GS]\n    \n    %% Glutamine Synthesis\n    AH(\\1) --> AI[GS Substrate Binding]\n    AJ(\\1) --> AI\n    AG --> AK[GS Catalysis]\n    AI --> AK\n    AK --> AL[ATP-Dependent Ligation]\n    AL --> AM[Glutamine Production]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 2: Other Ntr Genes\n    U --> ANDGATE2{NtrC-P AND<br/>Other Ntr Promoters?}\n    V --> AN[\u03c354 at Multiple Promoters]\n    AN --> ANDGATE2\n    \n    ANDGATE2 -->|Yes| AO[nac Gene Activation]\n    AO --> AP[NAC Transcription Factor]\n    AP --> AQ[Nitrogen Assimilation Genes]\n    AQ --> AR[Alternative N Source Utilization]\n    \n    %% High Nitrogen Path\n    L -->|No| AS[High Ammonia]\n    AS --> AT[Glutamine Synthesis]\n    AT --> AU[Glutamine Binds PII]\n    AU --> AV[PII-ADP-Glutamine]\n    AV --> AW[PII Binds NtrB]\n    AW --> AX[NtrB Phosphatase Activity]\n    AX --> AY[NtrC-P Dephosphorylation]\n    AY --> AZ[NtrC Inactive]\n    AZ --> BA[Low glnA Expression]\n    BA --> BB[Basal GS Levels]\n    \n    %% AND Gate 3: Feedback Loop\n    AM --> ANDGATE3{Glutamine AND<br/>PII Available?}\n    F --> ANDGATE3\n    ANDGATE3 -->|Yes| AU\n    \n    %% System Outputs\n    AM --> BC[Nitrogen Assimilation]\n    AR --> BD[Alternative N Sources Used]\n    BB --> BE[Ammonia-Sufficient Growth]\n    BC --> BF[Nitrogen Homeostasis]\n    \n    %% Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style J fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#ffd600,color:#fff\n    style M fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style N fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style O fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style P fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style R fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style S fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style X fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style ANDGATE1 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style Z fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AA fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AD fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AF fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AG fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AJ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AK fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style ANDGATE2 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AO fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AP fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AQ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AR fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AS fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AT fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AU fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AV fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AY fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AZ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BA fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style ANDGATE3 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style BC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BD fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style BE fill:#000000,color:#fff\n    style BF fill:#000000,color:#fff",
  "name": "Nitrogen Assimilation and Ntr Regulation",
  "notGates": 0,
  "notes": "This flowchart represents the Ntr system with 43 unique nodes (A-BF). Contains 2 OR logic gates (nitrogen status check, PII modification state) and 3 AND gates (\u03c354 activation requires NtrC-P enhancer AND RNAP-\u03c354; other Ntr genes require NtrC-P AND \u03c354; feedback requires glutamine AND PII). The system demonstrates \u03c354-dependent transcription (ATP-dependent open complex formation), PII signal transduction (2-ketoglutarate sensing), and two-component phosphorelay (NtrB-NtrC). All mechanisms validated against structural and biochemical studies.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_two_component_signaling",
    "ecoli_stringent_response",
    "ecoli_transcription_regulation"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on extensive research on nitrogen metabolism regulation, including structural studies of NtrC-\u03c354 complexes and the PII signal transduction mechanism. The Ntr system is one of the most thoroughly characterized examples of \u03c354-dependent regulation and two-component signal transduction. All regulatory mechanisms have been validated through genetic, biochemical, and structural studies.",
